===Noun===
{{en-noun|sg=[[ulterior]] [[motive]]}}

# An [[alternative]] or [[extrinsic]] [[reason]] for doing something, especially when concealed or when differing from the [[stated]] or [[apparent]] reason.
#* '''1895''', [[w:Arthur_Conan_Doyle|Sir Arthur Conan Doyle]], ''The Stark Munro Letters'', ch. 9,
#*: There lurks no bribe in the smell and beauty of the flower. Its charm has no '''ulterior motive'''.
#* '''1941''', "[http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,849702,00.html Poetry]," ''Time'', 8 Dec.,
#*: The poet is a man without a profit or any other kind of '''ulterior motive'''.
#* {{quote-book
|year=2006
|author=Philip Sington
|title=Zoia's Gold
|url=http://books.google.ca/books?id=CtaFbUVPFikC&dq=Zoia%27s+Gold
|isbn=0743291107
|page=197
|publisher=Scribner
|passage=I have an '''ulterior motive''', of course. I want a progress report on the catalog. You've been so mysterious about the whole thing, people are starting to talk.}}

